</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft"> <a href="/blog/poetry/bilingual-franco-moroccan-poem-kebir-m-ammi" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Ammi-Qotbi-a.jpg?itok=RjeD6jyF" width="100" height="75" alt="A black and white painting, mostly abstract, made up of elements that look like Arabic writing" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />
</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://www.worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/poetry/bilingual-franco-moroccan-poem-kebir-m-ammi">A Bilingual Franco-Moroccan Poem
</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">
Painting by Mehdi Qotbi (b. 1951, Rabat) / Courtesy of the artist
Les homeless
Les homeless ne vivent pas dans la rue
Ils attendent que le ciel se…
</div></div><span class="views-field views-field-field-date"><span class="field-content date-display-single">January 31, 2024
</span></span>|<span><span class="field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/kebir-m-ammi" hreflang="en">Kebir M. Ammi</a>
</span></span></div>
<div class="views-row"><div class="views-field views-field-field-blog-category"><div class="field-content field-name-field-blog-category"><a href="/blog-categories/essay" hreflang="en">Essay</a>
</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft"> <a href="/blog/essay/when-dogs-could-talk-among-words-state-grace-n-scott-momaday" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Momaday-Dogs-w.jpg?itok=QLiKdC-b" width="100" height="75" alt="A painting of a dog standing on a cloud" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />
</a>
